reviews.text: One of my favorites near my home. Get tsukemen and finish with additional soup or mixed-dry noodles.
The noodles super good
Delicious Ramen, a small typical Japanese ramen joint but be prepared to wait for a seat
Quick service, the ramen is amazing especially the soup. The chashui texture is good enough that I feel like it's very freshy.
A res proving real Japanese Ramen in Hong Kong

result.name: 台風

reviews.text: 普通麵量非常多，女士小朋友叫50%75%都量已足夠，因都的配料如叉燒亦都好多，以佢嘅價錢又唔收加一係其他地方根本冇可能。講完份量最重要當然味道，麵質爽口彈牙冇鹼水味，叉燒厚切夠淋又唔會好似肉乾咁，湯好濃郁飲完又唔會口乾。職員非常有禮，詳細講解唔同拉麵的分別，環境就好似傳統日本拉麵鋪咁圍主吧檯坐所以座位唔算多。
我本人超級喜燒這店的拉麵 配以濃醬油湯底 當然口味自己可以選擇 份量來說足夠飽 坐位已由高枱高櫈改為正常 一如往常單邊坐 沒有卡位 但亦不影響我品嘗美食的興致
座位不太舒服， 沾麵一流
很難食,員工太急,沒有用心
期間限定刀係好好味

result.adr_address: 39 Fife St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 39 Fife St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: Ramen Taifu

reviews.text: May not be the best I had but very tasty, the service is top and I loved the interior!

Lots of noodles but few toppings. Average ramen, pricier than it's worth.
We ordered from the DINNER menu. Perhaps the 4 star ratings are for the AFTERNOON menu.
Not the tastiest ramen in Hong Kong, but the restaurant is super Kawaii and the staff nice and spoke some English. Happy to give us a takeaway container.

I tried both the noodle with and without the soup. I liked both. The soup with the dry shrimp has a strong taste of the seafood and the one with tomato soup is a little bit sweet. The portion of the noodles is quite big.

One of the best Ramen in HK. This is not a super big brand but just a small one opened by a Japanese. The size of meal here is larger than normal and super tasty. If you a fans of Ramen, you should try this one out.

result.adr_address: 香港旺角快富街39號
result.name: Ramen Taifu

reviews.text: 好奇怪，google 評論好多人話义燒柴口，但也給5顆星，實際上义燒真的很柴，义燒邊也燒得不夠香，湯底有渣沬，不順滑，味道就見仁見智，喜歡鰹魚煙燻味，會覺得香，不喜歡就覺得苦，還有一個很奇怪，湯底有兩種溫度，上暖下熱，所以麵也上硬下軟，不知道是刻意，還是巧合，無論怎樣，我覺得這點不會加分，但是喜歡軟麵底的，一定會扣分。
非常不錯的小店， 值得一試
中午沾麵夜晚拉麵都好好味呀！正！（但係水準開始下降！叉燒粒少咗！反而荃灣店越做越好！)
燒海蝦味豚骨拉麵好味
每個月最少一次，唔食唔安樂～
